cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.NA, cs.GR, cs.SY 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category as the paper deals with Delaunay triangulations, which is a fundamental concept in computational geometry. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper presents an algorithm for perturbing a point set to improve the stability of the Delaunay triangulation. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is relevant as the paper discusses the quantifiable stability of the Delaunay triangulation with respect to the metric and point positions. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is a possibility as Delaunay triangulations are commonly used in computer graphics for mesh generation and surface reconstruction. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses stability guarantees for the resulting triangulation.
